      • getLastLastFolder

        public static java.lang.String getLastLastFolder​(java.io.File source)
        Enters to the source file if it is folder(otherwise if is file returns it), then looks for last folder in that folder then recursively check that last folder in the same way. However if the file precedes the folder priority will be given to the folder; that is if the last file in the folder is not directory then the final result will be that of returned by recursion
        Parameters:
        source - the source where to search
        Returns:
        the last file of the last folder of a source file

      • getLastLastFile

        public static java.lang.String getLastLastFile​(java.io.File source)
        Enters to the source file if it is folder(otherwise if is file returns it), then looks for last folder in that folder then recursively check that last folder in the same way. However if the file precedes the folder priority will be given to the files; that is if the last file in the folder is not directory then the final result will be that file
        Parameters:
        source - the source where to search
        Returns:
        the last file of the last folder of a source file
